              "text": ": ",
              "kind": "punctuation"
            },
            {
              "text": "CanvasSizingMode",
              "kind": "type"
            }
          ],
          "params": [],
          "returnType": null,
          "description": "How the canvas is sized within its parent (needs a parent via mount, or an element already in the DOM): - 'fixed' (default): exactly width×height. - 'fill': track the parent's size via ResizeObserver and re-render to fill it; width/height are the initial size. - 'fit': render at width×height and CSS-scale to fit the parent, preserving aspect ratio (letterboxed). - 'shrink': like 'fit' but never upscale beyond width×height — shrinks on smaller screens, stays native on larger ones. - 'letterbox': track the parent's size, render the backing store at the parent size × pixelRatio (always crisp, no CSS upscale-blur), and keep the camera locked to the fixed width×height design space, centered and letterboxed with bars (no crop, no stretch). The \"author once at a reference resolution\" model."
        },
